text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus gambleana is a species of tree in the beech family. It has been found in northeastern India and southwestern China (Guizhou, Hubei, Sichuan, Tibet, Yunnan).Quercus gambleana is a tree which grows to 20 meters (66 ft) tall. Leaves can be as much as 20 cm long (7.9 in).
